      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Blow-by Gas Reducer Structure - Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Blow-by gas generated in the crankcase is sucked in through the intake manifold via the PCV valve for combustion. This prevents the release of blow-by gas into the atmosphere. The breather chamber in the cylinder block separates the oil content of the blow-by gas and prevents oil from entering the combustion chamber."
    },
